FORMER Bafana Bafana captain Dean Furman has joined Northern Premier League Division one West side Warrington Rylands. Furman parted ways with Altrincham who campaign in the fifth tier of English football last week to join the Blues. Rylands announced via their twitter page that they have snatched the 33-year-old player who will add value in their team. Read the statement: “Ryan have announced that Dean Furman has joined the Blues. Dean possesses excellent technical ability, leadership, and experience at the very highest level, boasting 58 international caps for South Africa and can count Bradford City and Oldham Athletic among his former clubs. Welcome to Ryland Dean. “ Furman played the most (101) matches of his career while in the books of PSL side SuperSport United from 2015 until 2020 helping them to win the MTN8 trophy and two Nedbank Cups. 